; INSERT canonicalization: PullDataFromBeyondTrivialUnions hops the INSERT
; past a MERGE that collapses to a single distinct source (the self-recursive
; arm of `direct` merges the union with itself), while the two-message MERGE
; feeding out2 has two distinct sources and blocks the hop.

#message input(i32 A).
#message m2(i32 A).

#local direct(i32 A).
#local both(i32 A).

#query out1(free i32 A).
#query out2(free i32 A).

direct(A) : direct(A).
direct(A) : input(A).
out1(A) : direct(A).

both(A) : input(A).
both(A) : m2(A).
out2(A) : both(A).
